                            <comment id="13423780" author="ndrummond@rim.com" created="Fri, 27 Jul 2012 10:31:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;exception call stack&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13424089" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 27 Jul 2012 19:21:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;setting rows=null is the signal to stop looping over that inputsplit, so that&apos;s not going to work very well in the general case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13424753" author="ndrummond@rim.com" created="Mon, 30 Jul 2012 08:35:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah ok, thanks for the input. What&apos;s the best approach to solving this ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13425044" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 30 Jul 2012 17:46:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we can just add back the last-seen row.  Patch attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13425661" author="ndrummond@rim.com" created="Tue, 31 Jul 2012 10:32:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can confirm the patch works for our dataset. Thanks for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
